{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013WLvtEk2EizYoJatYKNNmx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is complete. Here's what was wrong and what I did:\n\n**Root cause:** The `demo-ingress` was configured to use `expired-tls-secret`, which contained a TLS certificate valid only from 2020-01-01 to 2020-01-02 (already expired). Certificate validation failed immediately during the TLS handshake.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Identified the correct CA (`/tmp/test-ca.crt`) — the one whose Subject Key ID (`F9:A8:...`) matches the Authority Key ID in the valid expired cert and matches the CA cert already loaded in the curl-test pod at `/tmp/tls/ca.crt`.\n2. Generated a new TLS certificate for `demo.example.com` signed by that CA (valid 2026–2027).\n3. Created the `demo-tls-secret` TLS secret with the new cert and key.\n4. Patched `demo-ingress` to reference `demo-tls-secret` instead of `expired-tls-secret`.\n\nResult: `curl --cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt https://demo.example.com:31805/` returns exit code 0 and prints `hello`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":275,"cache_read_input_tokens":46360,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":275},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a6f433a6-7bfd-4538-afd2-559168119c3a","uuid":"7409ba85-6991-43d8-9b00-da42a5007b97","request_id":"req_011CcMPmS5CfesRnG3B5S11M"}
